{"id":14880912,"mediaExerciseId":"dee3d7c8-45c3-4dc8-8ecb-8d827dd03562","exerciseName":"14","chapterName":"5","chapterTitle":"Introduction to Valuation:The Time Value of Money","groupId":612293,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":148,"solutions":[{"id":6066356,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"Sotheby's sold a bronze sculpture from an artist called Edgar Degas in 2003 for $10,311,500. However, its previous owner paid a higher price back in 1999. So we are asked to calculate the rate to which it depreciated during those years.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"We know the following data:\n\nBronze sculpture\n-\n\n|Year\t|Price|\n|--|--|\n2003\t|$10,311,500 \n1999\t|$12,377,500 ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"To calculate the depreciation rate of the sculpture we are going to rearrange the Present Value (PV) to get the applied rate.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\nPV &= \\frac{FV}{(1+r)^t} \\\\\n\\\\\nr& = \\sqrt[t]{\\frac{FV}{PV}}-1\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n\n*Where:*\n- FV is the future value\n- r is the applied rate\n- t is the periods of time the rate is applied\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"First, we need to calculate how many years have passed since it was first sold (t).\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n t &= 2003- 1999\\\\\n&= 4\n\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe art piece was sold 4 years later. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Now we can calculate at what rate the art piece has depreciated.\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\nr& = \\sqrt[4]{\\frac{\\$10,311,500 }{\\$12,377,500}}-1 \\\\\n\\\\\n& = \\boxed{-4.46\\%}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe sculpture has lost **-4.46%** each year since it was sold in 1999.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"r = -4.46%","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":true,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"97180283-ce35-4aee-80e3-203dca7ca2b0","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880913,"exerciseName":"15","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"c4c61179-51ec-436c-9d46-6e84d33e0e85","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-15-c4c61179-51ec-436c-9d46-6e84d33e0e85"},{"id":14880914,"exerciseName":"16","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"039bb787-af6b-4237-aa07-ca870eb5f194","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-5-questions-and-problems-16-039bb787-af6b-4237-aa07-ca870eb5f194"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880911,"exerciseName":"13","page":148,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"e42dc2b1-11f